{"ts":"2026-06-27T04:23:29.070Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing the Dashboard**\n\nI'm focusing on crafting a premium experience for the AI Operations page, specifically `/portal/ai-operations/page.tsx`. Currently, I'm at the layout stage, and working to define the metrics we'll be displaying. I have a couple of key ones in mind already. Specifically, I'm thinking about \"Total Active Agents\" and \"Average CPU Utilization\" as good initial pieces of data.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T04:23:30.049Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Expanding the Dashboard Metrics**\n\nI've expanded the planned metrics for the AI Operations page, incorporating \"Active Loops/Threads\" and \"Compliance Guardrails Status\". Also, I'm carefully reviewing the requirements and building out the structure of the `/portal/ai-operations` page. I am going to make it into the client-facing AI operations command center. Finally, I've got to ensure the UI has a premium look and feel.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T04:23:31.524Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining the Layout Structure**\n\nI'm now establishing the core framework for the AI Operations command center. I've broken down the design into interactive elements. We have interactive filter options. I am also working on: circular health rings using SVGs, and interactive tabs. There will be Tab 1: Agent Registry & Telemetry Cards. Tab 2: Governance & Compliance Policy. Tab 3: Enclave Runtime & Execution Timeline.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T04:23:33.572Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Adding the Oversight Link**\n\nI'm integrating an executive control panel into the AI Operations page, with a direct link to the Oversight Control Center. I am making it feel like a command center for the entire system! I'm also planning subtle motion transitions and am working on responsive layout. I will maintain a clean design using a premium color scheme and spacious layout, avoiding visual clutter. I've now checked to see if the routes are in place, and found the page listing! I am now ready to add the link in the header.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T04:23:36.030Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Implementing the Oversight Link**\n\nI've successfully integrated the \"Go to Control Center ->\" link, ensuring seamless navigation to `/portal/control-center`, addressing the oversight control requirement. I also checked the mock data models in `lib/mock-data-model.ts` and realized I can extend them for a high-fidelity page, while maintaining core type safety. Now, I'm designing the SVG health rings: I'm planning to make them circular progress bars with glowing gradients and drop shadows, to show CPU, memory, network/uptime, and thread load. Finally, I will implement dropdown filters for the project, agent type, status, and operating stage.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T04:23:37.764Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Adding Interactive Filters**\n\nI'm now implementing functional dropdown filters for project, agent type, and status, along with a search input. The goal is real-time list updates in response to user input. I'm focusing on ensuring these elements are highly interactive, and making sure the UI responds promptly to every change. I am confident in creating a full, high-fidelity implementation of the `/app/portal/ai-operations/page.tsx` soon, now that these interactive elements are in place. I have to design the mock data and types we need, and decided to do that right within the page. I'm also planning the layout and tabs.\n\nI am working on the page structure, and the Header Section will include Title: `AI Operations & Telemetry Command Enclave` and a description.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
